- "Education level" refers to the highest level of education attained;
- "Relationship status" includes various states such as married, single, etc.;
- "Occupation" refers to the specific job or profession;
- "Industry" refers to the sector of the economy in which one is employed;
- "Native country" refers to the country of origin or birth;
- "Race" and "gender" are demographic categories.

sql:
SELECT AVG(T1.median_income) 
FROM workclasses AS T1
WHERE T1.average_hours_per_week > 40;

SELECT education_name, employment_rate
FROM educations
ORDER BY employment_rate DESC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT education_id) AS count_of_education_levels
FROM educations
WHERE average_educational_num > 12;

external_knowledge:
