- "industries" refers to the different sectors of employment.;
- The "combined average income and employment rate" is the sum of the average incomes and employment rates for each demographic and industry category.;
- The "starting from the workclass with the lowest median income" indicates the hierarchical structure of the workclasses, built from the lowest median income upwards.

